newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: RTRS-Australia Dec car registrations fall 0.1 pct.
newsitem.headline: RTRS-Australia Dec car registrations fall 0.1 pct.

text.p: Australian new motor vehicle registrations fell a seasonally-adjusted 0.1 percent in December to 54,038, the Australian Bureau of Statistics said.
Economists had generally been looking for a small fall of around 2.0 percent.
The bureau said passenger vehicle registrations fell 1.4 percent in December, seasonally adjusted, while registrations for other vehicles rose 6.8 percent.
Total registrations were up 3.8 percent on the year.
